Something has to be done.  Erosion is everywhere.  The death of any great institution is by its excesses.<br>
Are we funding enough excess that we ignore or deprive the essential.. or can no longer afford the first class seat?<br>
I our efforts to be humane.. are we growing a ring of filth around those who work hard to pay taxes and raise children?<br>
Cookie talks about LAPD police officers throwing in the towel...Could it be because they don't like who they are making sacrifices for?  Maybe a few Top Guns are looking at the military and political whores that they have to work for and have decided to bale out.<br>
Could it be that our population of young americans can no longer honor a contract... with any one or any thing?  Can they no longer honor themselves?<br>
If you hold a foot race... are you required to give every runner a blue ribbon.. to keep from discriminating or hurting someone's feelings?  If you have a war... does every participant need to be called a hero.. at the expense of distracting from the acts of real heroes?<br>
It seems that we are killing off our high achievers by giving too much reward to the low achievers.<br>
I say, &quot;Raise the standards... cull the crop!  Make excellence a difficult thing to acquire (which it naturally is) and make it's acquisition a criteria for favor.<br>
No one should be held back because of the color of their skin or their gender... but no one should be given a free ride or advantage because of it.<br>
A lot of worthless people can waste more with a spoon than a good man can replace with a shovel!<br><br>
